The paper deals with tumor characterization from radiology images using machine learning techniques, specifically deep learning algorithms. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning algorithms to address the limited availability of labeled training data, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging applications, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of transfer learning, which falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
